    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In weaving; refers to the cords, wires, or steel strips that the warp passes through in a loom after passing through the reed, that allows the warp threads to be separated, allowing the shuttle to pass through the weft. Heddles are considered a major advance in the development of weaving technology.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Beim Weben bezieht es sich auf Schnüre, Drähte oder Stahlbänder, die die Webkette eines Webstuhls durchlaufen, nachdem sie das Riet durchlaufen haben; dies erlaubt den Kettfäden, getrennt zu werden, und dem Webschütz, durch den Schussfaden zu laufen. Litzen werden als bedeutender Fortschritt in der Entwicklung der Webtechnologie angesehen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>在紡織中，指稱織布機中的經紗在通過使經紗分開的筘齒後，所通過之粗線、金屬絲或鋼條，以使梭子穿過緯紗。一般認為，綜線是紡織科技發展的重大進步。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bij het weven; verwijst naar de koorden, draden of stalen strips waar de schering in een weefgetouw doorheen gaat na het passeren van de weefkam, waardoor de draden van de schering kunnen worden gescheiden en de spoelen door de inslag kunnen. Hevels worden beschouwd als een belangrijke vooruitgang in de ontwikkeling van de weeftechnologie.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
